content:
The surname "Downie" is of Scottish origin and is thought to derive from the Scottish Gaelic "dubhain," which means "little dark one." The name was likely originally given to someone with dark hair or a dark complexion.

In Scotland, the name was originally spelled "MacDhomhna," which means "son of the dark one." Over time, the name was anglicized and became "Downie."

It is now found as a surname throughout Scotland and in other countries, including England, Ireland, and the United States.
